In [99]:
plt.rcParams["figure.figsize"] = [13.00, 5.50]
plt.rcParams["figure.autolayout"] = True
columns = ["Location", "dBLevel"]
plt.xticks(rotation = 300)
plt.ylabel("dB level in dBm")
plt.xlabel("Location")
plt.figtext(1, 1, "Uplink Frequency: 15000 kbps")
plt.figtext(1, 1.04, "Downlink Fresquency: 30000 kbps")
plt.figtext(0.5, 1, "Linegraph between location and dBLevel")
plt.figtext(1, 1.08, "Phone Brand: REDMI")
plt.figtext(1, 1.12, "Model Number: M2003J15SI")
plt.figtext(1, 1.16, "Processor:octa-core MediaTek Helio G85")
plt.figtext(1, 1.20, "RAM: 4GB")
plt.plot(spreadsheet.Location, spreadsheet.dBLevel)
Out[99]:
[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x7f11452e5c70>]

As we know the signal is stronger the more the db level value approaches negative infinity, in the above graph we can see that the sites under Campus buildings are having more signal strength than the sites that are not, its highest at the point 'Under Construction' and lowest at the 'rooftop' of the building under Construction.¶
